expression.simple_expression:
"

This is a controller for an economizer, that adjusts the mixed air dampers to fulfill three control functions. It is based on Buildings.Examples.VAVReheat.BaseClasses.Controls.Economizer but edited to not use outside airflow measurement for outside air flow control and instead adjust the minimum outside air damper position based on fan speed linearly between support points assumed to be determined during commissioning.

  1. Freeze protection, based on the mixed air temperature measurement
  2. Minimum outside air requirement, based on supply fan speed.
  3. Supply air cooling, based on the logic implemented in Buildings.Examples.VAVReheat.BaseClasses.Controls.SupplyAirTemperature, with the additional condition that when the outside air dry bulb is greater than the return air dry bulb, economizer cooling is disabled.
"
